{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11571755]] Wikidata name: Prince Sahohiko [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:00, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Sahohiko no Mikoto''' (狭穂彦王, dates of birth and death unknown, died in the 10th month of the 5th year of Emperor Suinin's reign) was a member of the imperial family (royalty) in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] and [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]. In the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], he is referred to as '''Sahohiko no Mikoto''', while in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]], he is called '''Sahobiko no Mikoto''' (沙本毘古王).
== Overview ==
According to the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] and [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], in the 5th year of Emperor Suinin's reign, Sahohiko ordered his sister, [[:en:Saho-hime|Sahohime no Mikoto]], to assassinate the emperor. When the plan failed, he initiated a rebellion but was ultimately cornered. Both Sahohiko and his sister committed suicide within the fortifications of an earthen fortress made of rice sheaves. This rebellion, known as the {{ill|Rebellion of Sahohime and Sahohiko|ja|狭穂姫命#狭穂彦王の叛乱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rebellion of Sahohime and Sahohiko|qq=}}, is considered one of the most vividly described events in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]].
== Genealogy ==
The genealogy of Sahohiko is most detailed in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]]. According to it, he was the son of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikozahowake no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikozahowake no Mikoto|qq=}}, making him a grandson of [[:en:Emperor Kaika|Emperor Kaika]]. His mother was Sahono Ōkurumitoori (沙本之大闇見戸売), the daughter of Kasuga Takakuni Katsutorihime (春日建国勝戸売). He had several siblings, including {{ill|Ozaho no Ōkimi|lt=Ozaho no Ōkimi|lt=Oyamoto no Mikoto|ja|袁邪本王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oyamoto no Mikoto|qq=}}, the ancestor of Kudonowake and Kotoomi Kano, {{ill|Murobiko no Mikoto|ja|室毘古王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murobiko no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the ancestor of Wakasa Mimibetsu, and [[:en:Saho-hime|Sahohime no Mikoto]], who became the empress of Emperor Suinin. == See Also == * {{ill|List of people before the Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代以前の人物一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of people before the Asuka period|qq=}}
